%% Architecture Decision Record: LangChain Package Migration

%% This diagram visually documents a critical engineering decision made during
%% Phase 5 of the AutoResolve build: the migration away from legacy monolithic
%% libraries toward a modern, modular dependency strategy.
%% Key Architectural Concepts Represented:
%% - Legacy Monolithic Architecture: Historically, AI applications relied on
%%   langchain-community, a massive, bloated package containing hundreds of
%%   third-party integrations (OpenAI, Anthropic, LiteLLM, etc.). Installing this
%%   monolith in a production environment introduces severe risks, including
%%   dependency conflicts (which caused the Pytest errors in Phase 5), slower
%%   cold-start times, and an unnecessarily large attack surface.
%% - Modern Enterprise Architecture: The system now strictly utilizes langchain-core
%%   as the foundational engine. Integrations are handled via specialized, decoupled
%%   micro-packages (such as langchain-litellm). This approach guarantees strict
%%   version control, faster Docker image builds, and enhanced operational security
%%   by only installing the exact code the system executes.

graph TD
    subgraph Legacy Monolithic Architecture
        LC[langchain-community] --> O[OpenAI]
        LC --> A[Anthropic]
        LC --> L[LiteLLM]
        LC --> M[Many Others...]
    end

    subgraph Modern Enterprise Architecture
        Core[langchain-core] --> LCL[langchain-litellm]
        Core --> LCO[langchain-openai]
        LCL --> ChatLiteLLM
    end
